`,o.jsxs(r.p,{children:["A contract dependency is given by two things: its ",o.jsx(r.em,{children:"version"})," and its ",o.jsx(r.em,{children:"target"}),". The ",o.jsx(r.em,{children:"target"})," is the hash of ",o.jsx(r.em,{children:'"where the contract came from"'}),". We track targets inside of the ",o.jsx(r.code,{children:"cdm.json"})," so that contributors of a repository with a ",o.jsx(r.code,{children:"cdm.json"})," can freshly install all contract dependencies to their own environment (what you see in the GIF at the top of this post)-- a standard expectation for package managers."]}),`
